Mexico and Central America
---
Mexico (Veracruz state). 11 Apr 2018. (conf.) 10 Zika virus infected babies with microcephaly of 26 total microcephaly cases.
http://www.xeu.com.mx/nota.cfm?id=961078 [in Spanish]

South America
---
Brazil.
- Vector control. 25 Apr 2018. (reported) Millions of sterile mosquitoes will be released from drones over parts of Brazil to combat the Zika virus, after successful field tests were hailed as a "breakthrough" by the United Nations. Once freed, the sterilized, laboratory-bred male _Aedes aegypti_ mosquitoes mate with wild females, but do not produce viable eggs. The use of drones allows mosquitoes to be released by air on a large scale that reduces the cost of distribution.
https://www.reuters.com/article/brazil-health-zika/breakthrough-in-mosquito-packed-drones-to-combat-zika-in-brazil-idUSL8N1S17L4

- Congenital consequences. 15 May 2018. (reported) In the year since Brazil officially declared an end to the Zika outbreak, the aftermath has only just begun. An estimated 3000 children have Congenital Zika Syndrome, the collection of neurological disorders that afflict the babies of mothers infected with Zika during pregnancy. Civil Society in Brazil, with help from local and state governments, has done its best to explore new treatments for children as a response to the emergence of this new condition. But the number of children born with Congenital Zika Syndrome is straining Brazil's already limited public health system.
https://news.vice.com/en_us/article/evkdv7/inside-brazils-struggle-to-treat-thousands-of-kids-born-with-a-zika-linked-syndrome

[The social and economic consequences - for families and governmental agencies - of caring for these children is substantial and will continue well into the future. - Mod.TY]

Paraguay. 22 Apr 2018. (conf.) 2 cases in San Lorenzo, one each in the San Miguel and Tayasuapé neighborhoods.
http://www.abc.com.py/edicion-impresa/locales/salud-reporta-12-fallecidos-e-insiste-en-eliminacion-de-criaderos-de-mosquitos-1695515.html [in Spanish]

Peru. 9 May 2018. (reported) Peru has declared a national epidemiological alert to contain what appears to be an outbreak of the Guillain-Barré syndrome associated with the Zika virus, according to the country's health ministry. Health authorities suspect of more than 19 cases of the syndrome in Peru and have warned hospitals to watch for symptoms in other people.
https://www.reuters.com/article/us-peru-health/peru-declares-alert-over-suspected-guillain-barre-outbreak-idUSKBN1IA2LO

Asia
---
Bangladesh. 6 Apr 2018. (published) ZIKV-neutralizing antibodies were detected in a study from 2013 onwards. The prevalence of ZIKV-neutralizing antibodies was not significantly higher in patients with GBS compared to healthy. Serological evidence for prior ZIKV infection in patients with GBS was associated with more frequent cranial, sensory, and autonomic nerve involvement compared to GBS patients with _Campylobacter jejuni_, the predominant preceding infection in GBS worldwide. Nerve-conduction studies revealed that ZIKV antibodies were associated with a demyelinating subtype of GBS, while _C. jejuni_ infections were related to an axonal subtype. Interpretation: No significant association was found between ZIKV infection and GBS in Bangladesh, but GBS following ZIKV infection was characterized by a distinct clinical and electrophysiological subtype compared to _C. jejuni_ infection. These findings indicate that ZIKV may precede a specific GBS subtype but the risk is low.
https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/pdf/10.1002/acn3.556

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map showing the location of Bangladesh can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5800865,13276. - Mod.TY]

